      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are completely right that a stable patient on a consistent diet might not need the full 5mg, but you cannot guess the right dose without checking your INR first. Tapering down to 2mg or 2.5mg without monitoring could send your blood clotting levels into the danger zone where you risk a massive clot or stroke. Since your doctor is busy, call them immediately to request an urgent INR test or ask for a nurse to review your stability, but do not change your dose until you have that blood work.",
